Title: Machine Learning Approaches for Climate Change Prediction
Authors: Dr. Sarah Chen, Dr. James Rodriguez
Published: Nature Climate Change, Vol 42, March 2024
DOI: 10.1038/s41558-024-0001

Abstract:
This paper presents a novel deep learning framework for predicting regional climate
patterns using historical temperature, precipitation, and atmospheric CO2 data.
Our model achieves 94.2% accuracy on 10-year prediction windows, significantly
outperforming traditional statistical methods. We demonstrate the framework's
applicability across 15 distinct climate zones.

Keywords: machine learning, climate change, deep learning, prediction, neural networks
